--- ouroboros-seed-notes.md ---
# Ouroboros Seed Notes

These notes are seed material for downstream recursive planning tools. They are derived from a locked NI contract and are not an executable workflow.

Boundary rules:

- NI exports seed notes only.
- NI does not call Ouroboros or own Ouroboros state.
- Downstream state must remain outside NI and derived from the lock.

## Locked Contract Summary

- project_id: cli-fixture
- project_name: CLI Fixture
- purpose: Exercise namba-intent end.
- product_type: software
- delivery_surfaces: cli
- interaction_mode: human_to_system
- readiness_profile: prototype
- locked_readiness_status: READY
- locked_at: <TIMESTAMP>
- source_lock_hash: sha256:<SHA256>

## Capabilities

### CAP-001: Capability

- depends_on: none
- requirements: REQ-001 (Requirement)
- evaluations: EVAL-001 (Evaluation)
- risks: none
- artifacts: ART-001 (planning_docs at docs/plan/)

## Constraints

- Verify `.ni/plan.lock.json` exists and locked hashes match before using these notes.
- Preserve accepted requirements, risk mitigations, and blocker handling.
- Keep downstream state derived and outside NI core.
- Do not weaken acceptance criteria to make downstream work appear ready.

Accepted requirements:

- REQ-001: Requirement

## Risks

No risks are listed in the locked contract.

## Evaluation Contract

### EVAL-001: Evaluation

- method: fixture
- linked_capabilities: CAP-001

Evidence references:

- ART-001: planning_docs at docs/plan/

## Non-goals

- NG-001: Do not execute work.

## Target Non-goals

- Do not implement interview, crystallize, execute, evaluate, or evolve inside NI.
- Do not create an Ouroboros lifecycle, queue, or owned runtime state.
- Do not execute downstream agents.

## Source-of-Truth References

Source-of-truth order: .ni/plan.lock.json > .ni/contract.json > docs/plan/** > .ni/session.json > chat history

Locked files:

- .ni/contract.json sha256:<SHA256>
- docs/plan/00_project_brief.md sha256:<SHA256>
